Scythris valgella is a moth of the family Scythrididae. It was described by Bengt Å. Bengtsson in 2002. It is found in Iran, the United Arab Emirates, Yemen and Oman.The wingspan is 9.5–12 mm. The forewings are longitudinally striated in dark fuscous and whitish, a whitish plical streak most prominent. The hindwings are fuscous, paler near the base.